# Alchemyst AI — Document Update Cycle (TypeScript SDK)

## Background
Alchemyst AI is a context engine for AI agents. It ingests documents (chunking + embeddings) and exposes a vector search API. The platform treats `metadata.file_name` as a dedup key: re-adding a document whose `file_name` already exists fails with a `409 Conflict`. The supported way to refresh content is the **Delete-Then-Add** update cycle. See https://getalchemystai.com/docs/advanced/troubleshooting and the TypeScript Quickstart at https://getalchemystai.com/docs/getting-started/quickstart.

You will build a small Node.js + TypeScript CLI that exercises this full update cycle end-to-end against the real Alchemyst AI service using the official TypeScript SDK (`@alchemystai/sdk`). The CLI must compile to JavaScript and be runnable as `node dist/main.js`.

## Requirements
- Create a Node.js TypeScript project at `/home/user/update-task` that depends on `@alchemystai/sdk` and compiles to a `dist/` directory.
- The CLI takes no arguments and is invoked as `node dist/main.js`. A single invocation MUST exercise the full update cycle in order:
  1. Add a first version of a document ("v1").
  2. Attempt to add the same `file_name` again and confirm the platform rejects the duplicate with a `409 Conflict` (catch and log this; do NOT crash).
  3. Delete the existing document by `file_name`.
  4. Add a second version of the document ("v2") under the same `file_name`.
  5. Search the context engine for v2 and print the resulting content.
- The CLI MUST be safely rerunnable with the same `ZEALT_RUN_ID`: running it twice in a row must still complete the full cycle and finish with v2 indexed. Concretely, before step 1 the CLI MUST best-effort delete any pre-existing document with the run-scoped `file_name` so the initial add never trips a stale 409.
- All operations MUST be namespaced with `run-id` so concurrent CI runs do not collide. Read `run-id` from the `ZEALT_RUN_ID` environment variable, and use `policy-${run-id}.md` as the stored `metadata.file_name`.
- Credentials: Read `ALCHEMYST_AI_API_KEY` from the environment. Do **NOT** mock the SDK and do **NOT** hardcode credentials.
- The v1 content MUST mention `14-day` and the v2 content MUST mention `30-day` so that the post-update search result is unambiguous. The final stdout line printed by the CLI MUST contain the substring `30-day` and MUST NOT contain `14-day`.

## Implementation Hints
- Install the SDK with `npm install @alchemystai/sdk` and the TypeScript toolchain with `npm install -D typescript @types/node`.
- Add a `tsconfig.json` that emits to `dist/` (e.g. `"outDir": "dist"`, `"module": "commonjs"` or `"nodenext"`, `"target": "es2022"`). Provide an `npm run build` script that runs `tsc`.
- Construct the client with `new AlchemystAI({ apiKey: process.env.ALCHEMYST_AI_API_KEY })`.
- Use `client.v1.context.add` with `context_type: 'resource'`, `source: 'documentation'`, `scope: 'internal'`, and `metadata: { file_name: "policy-${run-id}.md" }` (snake_case for storage).
- Use `client.v1.context.delete` to remove the existing record by its `file_name` before re-adding. Inspect the SDK signature; targeting by `metadata.file_name` is the supported way to identify the document.
- Use `client.v1.context.search` with `similarity_threshold: 0.5`, `scope: 'internal'`, and a metadata filter keyed by `fileName: "policy-${run-id}.md"` (camelCase for search — this case asymmetry is intentional in the TypeScript SDK and is called out in the docs).
- The duplicate-add step is expected to fail. Wrap it in a try/catch and log a message that includes the substring `409` so it is observable; do NOT let the error abort the program.
- After a delete, allow a small propagation delay (e.g. ~2s) before re-adding to avoid indexing races. Similarly, after the v2 add, allow ~2s before searching.
- Print only one line to stdout at the very end: the `content` field of the top search result. That single line is what the verifier checks.

## Reference Documentation
- TypeScript Quickstart: https://getalchemystai.com/docs/getting-started/quickstart
- Troubleshooting (409 Conflict semantics): https://getalchemystai.com/docs/advanced/troubleshooting
- TypeScript SDK Tutorial: https://getalchemystai.com/docs/tutorials/typescript-agent.md
- Documentation index: https://getalchemystai.com/docs/llms.txt

## Acceptance Criteria
- Project path: /home/user/update-task
- Build command: `npm run build` (must produce `dist/main.js`).
- Command: `node dist/main.js`
  - Reads `ZEALT_RUN_ID` and `ALCHEMYST_AI_API_KEY` from the environment.
  - Performs add(v1) → duplicate add (observes 409) → delete → add(v2) → search, in that order, against the real Alchemyst AI service.
  - Best-effort deletes any pre-existing run-scoped document before step 1 so the command is rerunnable.
  - Exits with status 0.
  - The final line of stdout contains the substring `30-day` and does not contain `14-day`.
- The stored `metadata.file_name` MUST be exactly `policy-${run-id}.md` where `run-id` comes from the `ZEALT_RUN_ID` environment variable.
- Credentials are read from `ALCHEMYST_AI_API_KEY` only; the SDK is not mocked.


